    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="777"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">367N.11/104: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-07T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 7, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 7—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s October 6, 7 p.m. Affected American interests as Department is aware
                    are primarily Jewish.</p>
                <p>Our missionary and cultural interests are for the most part and our few Arab
                    Americans wholly sympathetic with Arab aspirations and not apprehensive as to
                    their security.</p>
                <p>Socony Vacuum installations are special problem which together with similar
                    installations other companies are receiving special Government
                    consideration.</p>
                <p>With particular reference to Jewish American lives and property interests there
                    can be no doubt that they are receiving same measure of protection afforded by
                    authorities within the means at their disposal to all other Jewish interests
                    both local and foreign. Special and helpful consideration is accorded all
                    specific requests made by this office.</p>
                <p>I gather clear impression in informal discussion with British officials that with
                    current arrivals of troop reenforcements strong suppressive action will be taken
                    against insurgent bands and extensively <pb facs="0959" n="951" xml:id="pg_951"
                    /> augmented measures instituted for the protection of Jewish and mixed areas
                    and reestablishment security on main highways.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
